## Idempotency Patterns

### Pattern 1: Check Before Write

```typescript
// WRONG: Assume job hasn't run
await tx.character.update({
  where: { id: characterId },
  data: { dailyCultivationClaimed: true },
});

// RIGHT: Check state before writing
const updated = await tx.character.updateMany({
  where: {
    id: characterId,
    lastDailyClaimedAt: { lt: todayStart }, // Only update if not claimed today
  },
  data: { lastDailyClaimedAt: new Date() },
});
if (updated.count === 0) {
  // Already claimed today — job was re-triggered, skip
  return { skipped: true, reason: "Already claimed today" };
}
```

### Pattern 2: Use Job ID for Deduplication

```typescript
// When adding a delayed job, use a deterministic job key
const jobKey = `seclusion:${characterId}:${Date.now()}`;
await seclusionQueue.add(
  "seclusion-complete",
  { characterId, expectedCompletionAt },
  {
    jobId: jobKey, // BullMQ uses jobId for deduplication
    delay: durationMs,
    removeOnComplete: 1000,
    removeOnFail: 5000,
  }
);
```

### Pattern 3: Upsert with Condition

```typescript
// For leaderboard refresh
await prisma.leaderboardEntry.upsert({
  where: {
    characterId_season: {
      characterId,
      season,
    },
  },
  update: {
    cultivationPoints: newTotal,
    updatedAt: new Date(),
  },
  create: {
    characterId,
    season,
    cultivationPoints: newTotal,
  },
});
```

