## Error Handling and Retry

### Retry Configuration

```typescript
const worker = new Worker("seclusion-complete", handler, {
  connection: redisConnection,
  concurrency: 5,
  limiter: {
    max: 10,
    duration: 1000,
  },
  attempts: 3,
  backoff: {
    type: "exponential",
    delay: 5000, // 5s, 10s, 20s
  },
  removeOnComplete: { count: 1000 },
  removeOnFail: { count: 5000 },
});
```

### Error Classification

| Error Type | Retry? | Action |
|-----------|--------|--------|
| Transient (network, Redis disconnect) | Yes (auto) | Log and retry |
| Data not found | No | Log as failed, alert |
| Validation error | No | Log as failed, alert |
| Partial state | Depends | Check idempotency, retry |

### Dead Letter Queue

Jobs that fail all retries go to the failed queue. Monitor this:

```typescript
failedWorker.process(async (job: Job) => {
  // Alert admins
  await sendAdminAlert(`Job ${job.name} (ID: ${job.id}) failed after ${job.attemptsMade} attempts`);
  // Log for manual review
  await prisma.failedJobLog.create({
    data: {
      jobName: job.name,
      jobData: job.data,
      attempts: job.attemptsMade,
      lastError: job.failedReason,
    },
  });
});
```

